reviews.review: Everything I wanted for the end of the Skywalker saga
Donâ€™t listen to the critics - this was a great movie!
I typically enjoy fan service, but this was too much fan service and not enough substance. Bundle that with a full blown ret-con of the Last Jedi and this movie crumbles under its own weight.

See the movie and decide for yourself. Since the controversy over The Last Jedi (which included bots trolling the ratings of that movie on this website), no review of this film should be taken as absolute truth. Attack of the clones has a 65% rating. Revenge of the Sith has an 80% rating. So take the score with a bit fat grain of sand...Everyone knows those are the worst Star Wars movies EVER.

Certainly in the weeks and months following the release of Rise of Skywalker, many people will try to explain to you why it sucks for this reason or that. It doesn't suck. It's a well made film, the acting is solid, the execution is solid and the plot is about as unoffensive as it could be given that it is trying to appease both Last Jedi haters and the rest of us who still like Star Wars. But overall, it threads the needle reasonably well and left me feeling satisfied. Daisy Ridley gives her best performance as Rey yet and the way they incorporated Carrie Fisher into the film felt was great. Leia is awesome in the movie!
This was a wonderful way to finish 42 years of tripletriology!

So hard to say how utterly disappointing these movies have become. How could something like this be so soul-less, so lacking in direction where every plot point must be explained away through dialogue, every emotional event is completely obliterated by a reversal moments later... I left the theater exhausted, confused, and disappointed.
It was a fun movie, but I felt like it didn't respect The Last Jedi.

Loved the movie. Been a fan since the early 90s when it was just the original trilogy. Movie was the most satisfying trilogy end yet, lots of fun twists and turns, story was well done, the trio of characters were all elevated to new heights. So excited for what the future holds.
